<font color="#FF0000">A CHRISTMAS PRESENT</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  7 17:33:27 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
There was an interesting story in our Oregonian on a seaman who lived through Pearl Harbor, then went on to become an aviator who was lost in the Pacific some years later.  His commentary about the preparredness of the Pacific Fleet for the Japanese drew parallels in my mind to our political handling of Vietnam.  <br><br>
I started a thread about giving back memories to the loved ones of those KIA and MIA.  Maybe we could focus some of our considerable talents to giving a Christmas present to the world in the form of good memories of those fallen men and women from Vietnam.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


